column1: Master of Science in Individualized Genomics and Health
column5: Experience an Innovative Education in Genomics on a Part-Time ScheduleBreakthroughs in genomics broaden our understanding of human health, disease prevention, and more. Prepare to support academia, research, and businesses in this growing field with Johns Hopkins University’s Advanced Academic Programs division. Whether part-time or full-time, the MS in Individualized Genomics and Health program can help you build the knowledge and skills for administrator roles, as well as further your expertise in advanced genomic research.
